text.section:
The following shall notify a victim of prohibited exposure or the victim's representative of the provisions of Part II of this subtitle:
a sexual assault crisis program established under § 11-923 of this title when a victim or victim's representative contacts the program;
an intake officer who receives a complaint for the alleged prohibited exposure under § 3-8A-10 of the Courts Article; or
on the filing of a charging document or delinquency petition for the alleged prohibited exposure:
the Department of State Police;
the Police Department of Baltimore City;
the police unit of a county;
the police unit of a municipal corporation;
the office of the sheriff of a county;
the office of the State's Attorney of a county;
the Office of the Attorney General;
the Office of the State Prosecutor;
the Department of Juvenile Services; or
the police unit of a bicounty unit or the University of Maryland.
